{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0c4cee5d-b75a-414f-9d39-3d36207c02ab","content":"The issue is classic F# — **file compilation order matters**. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on types defined in `Domain.fs`. F# requires dependencies to appear first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01RrzUa6nfUNDp52XfDhphb4","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01B8TVMbUXiybzgZaPPdwQEk","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-773b7435b37742958bccab54b450473b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-773b7435b37742958bccab54b450473b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"d24d19c6-8f6c-4794-88e1-a923ba52aa18","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nThe `.fsproj` lists:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order` type)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, so it needs `Domain.fs` to come first.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":448,"requestId":"7C2D:9E254:AA966E:C2FFD5:6A02792E"},"id":"23ccd912-5929-4f46-ac4f-a171c143bf42","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:58.086Z","parentId":"208f528b-2f9c-4ef0-a6c7-74623f612962"}
